# Windows Build Environment (MSYS2 UCRT64)

On Windows, the agent shell is PowerShell. Do **not** run `make`, `gcc`, or `scripts/*.sh` directly in PowerShell.

Run native C++ builds and bash scripts through MSYS2 **UCRT64** using the repo wrapper from the repo root:

```powershell
.\scripts\Invoke-Ucrt64.ps1 "cd src && make -j8"
.\scripts\Invoke-Ucrt64.ps1 "cd src && make run"
.\scripts\Invoke-Ucrt64.ps1 "./scripts/compile-commands.sh"
.\scripts\Invoke-Ucrt64.ps1 "./scripts/update-translations.sh"
```

MSYS2 root defaults to `C:\progs\msys2`. Override with the `MSYS2_ROOT` environment variable if installed elsewhere.

Use UCRT64 toolchain paths (e.g. `C:\progs\msys2\ucrt64\bin`) for gdb and related tools, matching `.vscode/launch.json`.
